ComBus_time:
Directly operated
Community Transit provided peak period commuter service both within Snohomish County and to destinations in King County.  In-county commuter service operated on weekdays between 4:45 AM and 5:00 PM.  Inter-county commuter service operated between 4:45 AM and 8:00 PM on weekdays.  There was no commuter service on weekends.
Purchased
Intercounty commuter service operated between 4:45 AM and 8 PM on weekdays.  There was no commuter bus service on weekends.
dem_time:
Community Transit provided dial-a-ride part-transit service to qualifying riders traveling to and from destinations within 3/4 mile of local Community Transit fixed routes during the hours of operation.
General hours of operation were between 5 AM and 11:00 PM Monday through Friday, and 6 AM to 10:00 PM on Saturdays.  If travel was required outside of Community Transit's local fixed-route service area, Community Transit coordinated the trip with other para-transit providers in the region.  There was no demand response service on Sundays.
fix_time: Community Transit provided local fixed route service in Snohomish County.  Local fixed route service operated on weekdays between 5 AM and 11:00 PM and on Saturdays between 6 AM and 10:00 PM.  There was no local fixed route service on Sundays.
van_time: Community Transit had 366 vans on the road in 2013.  Community Transit had a total of 414 vehicles in the fleet:  2 nine passenger vans with a mobility lift, 285 seven passenger vans, 75 twelve passenger vans and 52 fifteen passenger vans.  These vanpools had origins and/or destinations in Snohomish, King, Island, Skagit, Kitsap and Pierce counties.

Dial-A-Ride: A complementary paratransit
service for ADA certified individuals who are
unable to utilize the fixed-route bus system.
Job Access provides transportation for work
activities to those who meet federal income
guidelines. Operates daily between 5:00 am
and 11:30 pm. Job access trips are
provided on Valley Transit's Fixed-Route,
Dial-A-Ride, and Evening and Saturday
Services during normal operating hours.
Job access trips outside normal operating
hours are provided using a reservationbased
demand-responsive system.
